'''Tahsin Mohammed Jamshid''' (born 16 June 2006) is a Qatari professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Qatar Stars League]] club [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] and the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/top-stories/indian-origin-teenage-footballer-tahsin-included-in-qatar-squad/articleshow/110550578.cms|title=Indian-origin teenage footballer Tahsin included in Qatar squad|work=The Times of India |date=30 May 2024|via=The Economic Times – The Times of India|access-date=1 June 2024|archive-date=30 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530172329/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/top-stories/indian-origin-teenage-footballer-tahsin-included-in-qatar-squad/articleshow/110550578.cms|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Early life==
Tahsin was born on 16 June 2006 in Qatar to Indian [[Malayalis|Malayali]] parents from [[Kerala]]. He got into football under his father's guidance, who was a former [[University of Calicut]] footballer. Tahsin's father Jamshid hails from [[Thalassery]] and mother Shyma hails from [[Valapattanam]]. His father works as an accountant in Qatar. Tahsin trained at the Aspire Football Academy in Qatar and became the first Indian-origin player in the Gulf nation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onmanorama.com/sports/football/2024/05/30/kannur-lad-makes-qatar-squad-world-cup-qualifiers.html|title=Kannur lad makes it to Qatar squad for World Cup qualifiers|website=Onmanorama|access-date=1 June 2024|archive-date=30 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530165507/https://www.onmanorama.com/sports/football/2024/05/30/kannur-lad-makes-qatar-squad-world-cup-qualifiers.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Club career==
Tahsin started playing [[association football|football]] in the Qatar Stars League. He made his senior debut for Al Duhail on 31 March 2024 against Al Rayyan,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://khelnow.com/football/indian-football-tahsin-mohammed-jamshid-qsl-202404|title=Tahsin Mohammed Jamshid becomes first Indian-origin player to play in Qatar Stars League|website=Khel Now|access-date=1 June 2024|archive-date=2 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402131319/https://khelnow.com/football/indian-football-tahsin-mohammed-jamshid-qsl-202404|url-status=live}}</ref> he plays as a left winger, has trained at the Aspire Football Academy in Qatar and has featured in various age group squads in Qatar. He was part of the Qatari U-16, U-17<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.gulf-times.com/story/725691/qatar-qualify-for-u-17-asian-cup-2023|title=Qatar qualify for U-17 Asian Cup 2023|date=9 October 2022|website=Gulf Times|access-date=1 June 2024|archive-date=26 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221026181757/https://www.gulf-times.com/story/725691/Qatar-qualify-for-U-17-Asian-Cup-2023|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Qatar national under-17 football team|Qatar U-17 football team]]s.<ref>{{cite web | title=Team Qatar qualify to AFC U17 Asian Cup Finals | url=https://www.olympic.qa/media-center/team-qatar-qualify-afc-u17-asian-cup-finals#:~:text=Muscat%3A%20Qatar%20advanced%20to%20the,of%20the%20Qualifiers%20on%20Sunday }}</ref>
He made his debut for Al Duhail in the Qatar Stars League, the country's first division football, becoming the first footballer of Indian origin to play in the league.

==International career==
Tahsin was named in the senior Qatar squad<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://x.com/QFA_EN/status/1795529329226690632?t=RPXj2i8J9hnBIXXyQJpIeg&s=19 |title=Archived copy |access-date=1 June 2024 |archive-date=1 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240601141025/https://x.com/QFA_EN/status/1795529329226690632?t=RPXj2i8J9hnBIXXyQJpIeg&s=19 |url-status=live }}</ref> for Qatar's matches against Afghanistan and India in FIFA World Cup Qualifiers Group A on 6 and 11 June.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.duhailsc.qa/news/35870/|title=Four Players from Al Duhail in Qatar National Team… – Duhail Sports Club|website=www.duhailsc.qa|access-date=1 June 2024|archive-date=30 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530190340/https://www.duhailsc.qa/news/35870/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.qfa.qa/coach-marquez-announces-squad-ahead-of-world-cup-qualifiers/|title=Coach Marquez announces squad ahead of World Cup qualifiers|first=Abualabass|last=Mustafa|date=29 May 2024|website=Qatar Football Association|access-date=1 June 2024|archive-date=1 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240601140722/https://www.qfa.qa/coach-marquez-announces-squad-ahead-of-world-cup-qualifiers/|url-status=live}}</ref>

